					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5381818#post-3726847</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5381818/scp-3787#post-3726847</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 02 Mar 2018 21:35:03 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>updogg</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3736020</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I have to say, reading this left me in utter confusion. It's written well enough, but I don't know what the heck this is supposed to mean or if it's a reference, or something else. The rubber horses (that for some bizarre reason like to form wheels??) felt absolutely random and out of nowhere and didn't seem to have any relation to the rest of the anomalies. Why are people transforming into horses, or gaining horse-like features, seemingly out of nowhere? The Foundation's plan to build an SCP-2000 but specifically for horses seemed equally bizarre, and I had a hard time believing that they'd do something that extreme. I didn't really appreciate the cross-references; in my opinion, they seem somewhat tacked on, as in you looked at the Equine tag and stuffed whatever you found into the article, which, while that wouldn't necessarily be a bad thing, I don't think it works very well here. Finally, I must have missed it, but I'm not sure how exactly this counts as Hiemal anomaly, as I didn't catch anything that would point towards self-containment between any two of the anomalies, but I might have just missed it.</p> <p>I gave a downvote here, because while it's written in a professional manner, I seriously have no idea what to make of this. It came off as random for random's sake from my perspective. If you were meaning to expand on this, I could easily change my vote, but right now, I can't say I can appreciate this article.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5381818#post-3725767</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5381818/scp-3787#post-3725767</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 01 Mar 2018 18:12:35 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Weryllium</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2727655</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">I still don't like Hiemal</span></p> <p>I remember all the way back when you first pitched the squiggly squishy horse-things. I can definitely say this finished product was well worth the wait. Very unsettling and continually ramps up, without ever becoming stale or over-the-top.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5381818#post-3725752</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5381818/scp-3787#post-3725752</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 01 Mar 2018 17:48:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TL333s</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1304786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>That was insane. I can't remember the last time I saw an anomaly build and build on itself like this for this long. <em>In the future, there will be horses.</em> <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">But are these doublehorses or antihorses?</span></p> <p>You do reach semantic saturation with 'horse' a good third of the way through this, but then I got to</p> <blockquote> <p>This is the emergence of an intense fear of horses among humans with no previous basis to fear horses.</p> </blockquote> <p>and I'm like, &quot;Oh shit, I have this.&quot; And that makes me wonder if the popularity of My Little Pony was engineered by the Foundation to prevent the spread of epsilon. But since this is in the future, it's Generation 5 by that point. <em>Hasbro failed humanity.</em> D:</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5381818#post-3725555</guid>
				<title>Re: 2nd SCP &quot;The Horse Meme&quot;</title>
